# {{ .name }}

ASP.NET Minimal API sample that publishes a message with Dapr pub/sub and receives it through a subscribed endpoint.

## Run

```bash
dapr run \
  --app-id {{ .appId }} \
  --app-port 5001 \
  --dapr-http-port 3500 \
  --resources-path ./local/dapr-components \
  -- dotnet run --project ./src --urls http://localhost:5001
```

## Endpoints

- `POST /publish` - the public route you call; accepts an `OrderIn` (`{ "orderId": "...", "customerId": "...", "amount": 0 }`) and publishes it to Dapr pub/sub component `pubsub`, topic `messages`.
- `POST /subscribe` - not a route you call; subscribed to `pubsub/messages`, Dapr invokes it for each message and runs it through the send pipeline.
- `GET /dapr/subscribe` - generated by Dapr.AspNetCore to expose subscriptions to the Dapr sidecar.

Use `src/{{ .name }}.http` to send a sample request.
